    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-11-12T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-11-12T08:00:00-05:00" n="463"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/1170: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-11-12T13:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1925—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>559. Your 421, November 11, 5 p.m. I have always had a perfect understanding of
                    the attitude of the American Government regarding the service of American
                    citizens in armed forces in Morocco, and I have governed myself accordingly. I
                    have never at any time had any sort of communication with them nor has there
                    ever been any question of any sort of official recognition. In fact I fail to
                    understand the cause of your 421.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
